  "prompt": "What is the best time of day to drink a single coffee to keep you going for the longest duration?",
  "response": "The best time of day to drink coffee for optimal energy varies somewhat depending on individual sleep patterns and daily schedules. However, common recommendations suggest consuming coffee mid-morning, between 9:30 and 11:30 AM. This timing aligns with natural dips in cortisol levels (a hormone related to alertness) and can help you stay focused and energized without interfering with your natural circadian rhythms or sleep patterns later in the day.\n\nKeep in mind that factors such as individual tolerance to caffeine, overall health, and the specific timing of daily activities can influence the best personal coffee timing. It's also important to ensure that coffee consumption doesn't occur too late in the day, as it can interfere with sleep quality and overall energy levels.",
